The first way is achieved on the World Wide Web by using one the many available search engines (such as Altavista, Lycos, or InfoSeek), and the second way is mainly achieved by browsing the WWW, following predefined links between documents. Most of the people tend to move between these two modes depending on the task to perform. Nowadays, most users are facing difficulties using the existing tools to achieve satisfaction in their information seeking task. We think that the two main problems inherent to the WWW, which are behind these problems, are :